00:07:26,173 --> 00:07:28,174
and Hamilton said, you know, I've always wanted to play

167
00:07:28,194 --> 00:07:32,117
a turn-based strategy game with the backgammon doubling cube.

168
00:07:33,098 --> 00:07:36,220
And so I booted up Hearthstone, and every turn of the game,

169
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:39,423
Hamilton said, would you double the cube right now?

170
00:07:39,943 --> 00:07:42,345
If your opponent doubled the cube, would you concede?

171
00:07:43,206 --> 00:07:47,869
And we got to immediately feel the impact of that mechanic

172
00:07:47,909 --> 00:07:49,791
without having to build anything.

173
00:07:50,682 --> 00:07:54,025
And through those initial playtests, we realized a couple things about this doubling mechanic.

174
00:07:54,805 --> 00:07:56,467
It increased the emotional range, right?

175
00:07:56,487 --> 00:08:00,330
Instead of just one star per match, you're playing for potentially a lot more stars.

176
00:08:01,151 --> 00:08:02,752
We spent less time losing, right?

177
00:08:02,792 --> 00:08:06,896
In a normal game, if you have like a 5% chance to win, you've got to play that all the way out, right?

178
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:07,917
Because you might win.

179
00:08:08,537 --> 00:08:12,981
And that period of time where you're like probably going to lose can be pretty grueling.

180
00:08:13,422 --> 00:08:15,143
Like the final six hours of a game of Monopoly.

181
00:08:16,966 --> 00:08:19,968
But when you're incentivized to bail out because you're going to lose less cubes,

182
00:08:19,988 --> 00:08:23,249
you can just leave and you spend less time in that grueling zone.

183
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:26,611
Games that you don't play all the way to completion are faster, obviously.

184
00:08:27,451 --> 00:08:31,654
But there was two other things that I think had a really big impact that I'm going to dig into a little bit more.

185
00:08:32,154 --> 00:08:34,355
So the first is zero sum is zero fun.

186
00:08:34,695 --> 00:08:37,877
If two players play a game and one of them wins and the other loses,

187
00:08:38,297 --> 00:08:45,561
and it is as fun to win as it is not fun to lose, you have created net zero joy.

188
00:08:46,515 --> 00:08:50,196
You just moved happiness from one person to another.

189
00:08:51,816 --> 00:08:54,317
So we were trying to avoid this situation.

190
00:08:54,337 --> 00:08:55,697
There's a bunch of ways to tackle this.

191
00:08:56,257 --> 00:08:57,297
The first is bots.

192
00:08:57,578 --> 00:08:59,178
It's one of the easiest ways to avoid zero-sum

193
00:08:59,218 --> 00:09:00,758
because you just have a player who's winning

194
00:09:00,798 --> 00:09:01,439
and nobody's losing.

195
00:09:01,459 --> 00:09:04,179
So I really like PUBG Mobile.

