214
00:09:51,350 --> 00:09:58,515
So at GDC 2014, my mentor and the original game director of Hearthstone, Eric Douds, gave a talk about Hearthstone design values.

215
00:09:58,875 --> 00:10:00,176
He talked about little victories.

216
00:10:01,162 --> 00:10:03,985
The big victory is whether you win or lose the game.

217
00:10:04,625 --> 00:10:06,487
And the little victories are things that happen

218
00:10:06,527 --> 00:10:08,169
during the game, anything that makes you feel smart

219
00:10:08,229 --> 00:10:08,729
or powerful.

220
00:10:08,769 --> 00:10:10,171
So imagine playing a game of Counter-Strike

221
00:10:10,891 --> 00:10:12,072
and you come out of this spawn point

222
00:10:12,092 --> 00:10:13,173
and someone headshots you and you die.

223
00:10:13,647 --> 00:10:16,909
You had no moment where you felt smart or powerful during that game.

224
00:10:17,149 --> 00:10:19,191
But let's imagine you're playing the game of Counter-Strike and you run out

225
00:10:19,211 --> 00:10:20,933
and you're just blowing up everyone on the enemy team,

226
00:10:21,033 --> 00:10:24,616
and eventually you lose, but you still felt, like, awesome while you were doing it.

227
00:10:25,436 --> 00:10:26,257
That's little victories.

228
00:10:26,697 --> 00:10:30,681
So, essentially, little victories add a little joy, even if you lose.

229
00:10:31,321 --> 00:10:35,642
So on Hearthstone, we avoided cards that blow up enemy mana crystals or force your opponent to discard cards

230
00:10:36,042 --> 00:10:40,083
because they could potentially create scenarios where you never get to feel powerful.

231
00:10:40,543 --> 00:10:43,183
And in Marvel Snap, there's six turns. You always get to play six turns.

232
00:10:43,203 --> 00:10:47,464
You always get to do something. You get to play some of your cards and feel a little bit powerful while you do it.

233
00:10:49,484 --> 00:10:54,325
But the cube had one of the biggest impacts on the zero-sum paradigm.

234
00:10:55,346 --> 00:10:57,186
So we found that when your opponent snaps...

235
